@changleicn thanks for the clarification. Please update https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HAWQ-760 to state that this is specifically intended to move/load data into the HAWQ tablespace.
Also, w.r.t to data loading/ingestion it would be cleaner if we stick to the standard sql approaces such as MYSQL's LOAD DATA http://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.7/en/load-data.html or Postgres COPY FROM https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/static/sql-copy.html.
Moving a file from one location to HAWQ' tablespace effectively has the same work as copying the file. Also, the advantage with using LOAD/COPY is we still stick to the SQL approach as opposed to introducing an external shell script from data copy/moving.
